// Same finding as static_cast_between_scalar_types_is_not_supported.scpp,
// for the C-style cast spelling instead of `static_cast`: `(int)b` is
// also rejected ("expected an expression but found 'int'"). Real C++
// accepts both spellings for this kind of conversion; scpp's docs don't
// call out a preference for one over the other (ch06 scalar table just
// says "requires an explicit cast"), so both are worth checking.
int main() {
    bool b = true;
    int x = (int)b;
    return x;
}
